The JIRA REST API uses a JSON string with unspecified element names for custom fields.

{code}
{
  ... 
  "fields":
  {
    "customfield_10610":
    {
       ...
{code}

This is not parseable by some frameworks.

It would be better to write it as an array.

{code}
{
  "fields":
  {
    "customfields":
    [
      {
        "id":"customfield_10610",
        "name":"example",
        "value":"1.5"
      },
      {
        "id":"customfield_10620",
        ...
      },
      ...
    ]
 {code}

